# Ingredients
3 eggs, separated
3 tablespoons powdered sugar
1/2 teaspoon ground allspice
1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon
1/2 teaspoon ground cloves
4 ounces brandy, lukewarm <-- Tweak available here
3 cups hot milk
Freshly grated nutmeg

# Steps

1 In a large, clean bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.
2 In a separate bowl, beat the egg yolks until light in color; gradually beat in the sugar, allspice, cinnamon, and cloves. Fold the yolk mixture into the whites.
3 Pour 2 tablespoons into four mugs each. Add 1 ounce brandy and 1 ounce dark rum to each mug.
4 Fill with hot milk. Stir well, and dust with nutmeg.

